comments.author: BitMaxz
comments.body: There seems to be an issue with your hashboard related to EEPROM, and the logs show an sn error. Probably because the EEPROM is different or corrupted or maybe you have a different hashboard or recently replaced it with a new one?Can you try to test all hash boards one by one to find which hash board that causing this error?And hope that you can edit your thread it looks messy you can use the insert code tag to put all your logs properly.

comments.author: EastCoastASICRepair
comments.body: First, I would try a SD flash. Try running the miner with a third party firmware like Braiins if this error persists. You could also rewrite the EEPROM with a skypro if you have a good bin file.
